-- AC Milan Keeps Up Pace Atop Italy's Serie A; Barcelona Leads Real in Spain
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-12-12T23:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-12/ac-milan-keeps-up-pace-atop-italy-s-serie-a-real-madrid-wins-in-spain.html
AC Milan kept up the pace at the top
of Italian soccer’s Serie A with a 3-0 win at Bologna yesterday.  Kevin-Prince Boateng ,  Robinho  and  Zlatan Ibrahimovic  got
the goals as Milan improved to 36 points, six more than Napoli
and Lazio, which lost 2-1 at Juventus in the late game.  Matches went ahead in Italy this weekend after a threatened
player strike was called off.  Real Madrid won 3-1 at Real Zaragoza to temporarily take
the lead in the Spanish standings before Barcelona restored its
two-point advantage with a 5-0 win over Real Sociedad in
yesterday’s late match.  Borussia Dortmund leads Germany’s Bundesliga by 11 points
after a 2-0 win over Werder Bremen two days ago. Mainz lost 1-0
at home to Schalke yesterday and dropped to fourth behind Bayer
Leverkusen and Hanover.  Lille leads the French standings after a 1-0 win at Arles
Avignon two days ago.  In the Netherlands, FC Twente lost 6-2 at Heerenveen
yesterday, failing to take advantage of PSV Eindhoven’s 0-0 draw
at De Graafschap two days ago. Leader PSV has 38 points, a point
more than Twente.  WEEKEND RESULTS
===============
Italy: Genoa 0-1 Napoli; Palermo 3-1 Parma; Udinese 2-1
Fiorentina; Bologna 0-3 AC Milan; Brescia 1-0 Sampdoria;
Cagliari 3-0 Catania; Lecce 3-2 Chievo; Roma 1-0 Bari, Juventus
2-1 Lazio.  Spain: Atletico Madrid 2-0 Deportivo La Coruna; Getafe 1-0
Villarreal; Sevilla 1-3 Almeria; Athletic Bilbao 2-1 Espanyol;
Hercules 4-1 Malaga; Mallorca 0-1 Racing Santander; Real
Zaragoza 1-3 Real Madrid; Sporting Gijon 1-1 Levante, Barcelona
5-0 Real Sociedad. Dec. 13: Valencia vs Osasuna.  Germany: Hanover 2-1 Stuttgart; Bayern Munich 3-0 St. Pauli;
Borussia Dortmund 2-0 Werder Bremen; Cologne 1-0 Eintracht
Frankfurt; Kaiserslautern 0-0 Wolfsburg; Hamburg 2-4 Bayer
Leverkusen; Hoffenheim 1-1 Nuremberg; Mainz 0-1 Schalke;
Freiburg 3-0 Borussia Moenchengladbach.  France: Nancy 1-0 Sochaux; Arles-Avignon 0-1 Lille; Auxerre 1-1
Marseille; Brest 0-0 Montpellier; Caen 0-0 Nice; Lorient 3-0
Lens; Valenciennes 1-2 Paris Saint-Germain; Lyon 2-0 Toulouse;
Monaco 0-2 St. Etienne, Bordeaux 0-0 Rennes.  Netherlands: Heracles 2-2 VVV Venlo; De Graafschap 0-0 PSV
